[00:07.90]	So full of ugly sights, of ghastly dreams,
[00:11.16]	That, as I am a Christian faithful man,
[00:14.21]	I would not spend another such a night,
[00:17.33]	Though 'twere to buy a world of happy days,
[00:20.65]	So full of dismal terror was the time!
[00:23.71]BRAKENBURY	What was your dream? I long to hear you tell it.
[00:27.38]CLARENCE	Methoughts that I had broken from the Tower,
[00:30.85]	And was embark'd to cross to Burgundy;
[00:33.90]	And, in my company, my brother Gloucester;
[00:37.09]	Who from my cabin tempted me to walk
[00:40.07]	Upon the hatches: thence we looked toward England,
[00:43.88]	And cited up a thousand fearful times,
[00:46.93]	During the wars of York and Lancaster
[00:49.98]	That had befall'n us. As we paced along
[00:53.10]	Upon the giddy footing of the hatches,
[00:56.15]	Methought that Gloucester stumbled; and, in falling,
[01:00.03]	Struck me, that thought to stay him, overboard,
[01:03.57]	Into the tumbling billows of the main.
[01:06.62]	Lord, Lord! methought, what pain it was to drown!
[01:10.22]	What dreadful noise of waters in mine ears!
[01:13.62]	What ugly sights of death within mine eyes!
[01:17.02]	Methought I saw a thousand fearful wrecks;
[01:20.35]	Ten thousand men that fishes gnaw'd upon;
[01:23.60]	Wedges of gold, great anchors, heaps of pearl,
[01:27.07]	Inestimable stones, unvalued jewels,
[01:29.91]	All scatter'd in the bottom of the sea:
[01:33.03]	Some lay in dead men's skulls; and, in those holes
[01:36.85]	Where eyes did once inhabit, there were crept,
[01:40.38]	As 'twere in scorn of eyes, reflecting gems,
[01:43.71]	Which woo'd the slimy bottom of the deep,
[01:46.97]	And mock'd the dead bones that lay scatter'd by.
[01:50.71]BRAKENBURY	Had you such leisure in the time of death
[01:54.04]	To gaze upon the secrets of the deep?
[01:57.02]CLARENCE	Methought I had; and often did I strive
[02:00.14]	To yield the ghost: but still the envious flood
[02:03.81]	Kept in my soul, and would not let it forth
[02:07.21]	To seek the empty, vast and wandering air;
[02:10.47]	But smother'd it within my panting bulk,
[02:13.66]	Which almost burst to belch it in the sea.
