[08:03.07]First Murderer	Hark! he stirs: shall I strike?
[08:05.50]Second Murderer	No, first let's reason with him.
[08:08.06]CLARENCE	Where art thou, keeper? give me a cup of wine.
[08:11.53]Second murderer	You shall have wine enough, my lord, anon.
[08:14.72]CLARENCE	In God's name, what art thou?
[08:17.08]Second Murderer	A man, as you are.
[08:18.67]CLARENCE	But not, as I am, royal.
[08:20.61]Second Murderer	Nor you, as we are, loyal.
[08:22.69]CLARENCE	Thy voice is thunder, but thy looks are humble.
[08:26.30]Second Murderer	My voice is now the king's, my looks mine own.
[08:29.83]CLARENCE	How darkly and how deadly dost thou speak!
